by SpacePossum at 2016-04-13T07:09:03Z

>We should probably allow fixers themselves to know what they conflict with, otherwise we have incorrect measures in place for when people add custom fixers.

Good point, I had discussed this with @keradus already and while it is an interesting solution it is also harder to make and maintain. If we would build that conflicting fixers would be aware of each other, both ways. This PR provides one solution, but indeed lacks the option to deal with custom fixers.

>Also, we should mark the proxy fixers as conflicting with the fixer they proxy?

I'm not sure what you mean, i.e. what issue is there?

